commit.message:
exfatprogs: release 1.2.2 version

exfatprogs 1.2.2 - released 2023-10-26
======================================

CHANGES :
 * exfat2img: Allow dumps for read-only devices.
 * fsck.exfat: Revert Repairing zero size directory.

NEW FEATURES :
 * fsck.exfat: Repair duplicated filename.
 * mkfs.exfat: Add the option "q" to print only error messages.
 * mkfs.exfat: Add the option "U" to set volume GUID.
 * tune.exfat: Add the option "U" / "-u" to set or print volume GUID.

BUG FIXES:
 * fsck.exfat: Fix some out-of-bounds memory accesses.
 * fsck.exfat: Change not to delete volume GUID directory entry.

Signed-off-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

exfat2img: fix out-of-bounds write in read_file_dentry_set

if SecondaryCount is greater than (2 + the max number
of File Name entries), writing to memory outside
the node->name could happen.

Reported-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Signed-off-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: fix out-of-bounds write in read_file_dentry_set

if SecondaryCount is greater than (2 + the max number
of File Name entries), writing to memory outside
the node->name could happen.

Reported-by: Maxim Suhanov <dfirblog@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

manpages: add usage for volume GUID

This commit adds option -U to mkfs.exfat manpage and add
option -U/-u to tune.exfat manpage.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: do not treat volume GUID entry as unknown entry

The Volume GUID exists as a benign primary directory entry
in the root directory and should not be deleted as an unknown
directory entry.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

mkfs: support set volume GUID

This commits adds support for adding volume GUID in mkfs.exfat.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

tune: support volume GUID

This commit adds support for adding, deleting, modifying and
showing volume GUID in tune.exfat.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

lib: add helpers for volume GUID

This commit adds 3 helpers for volume GUID.
  - exfat_read_volume_guid()
  - exfat_set_volume_guid()
  - __exfat_set_volume_guid()

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

lib: support get the first empty dentry set position

This commit adds ->in.dentry_count to exfat_lookup_filter.

If ->in.dentry_count is 0, the function of exfat_lookup_dentry_set()
has no change. After calling exfat_lookup_dentry_set(), if the dentry
set is not found, ->out.dev_offset will be the position of the last
empty dentry set.

If ->in.dentry_count is not 0, the function of exfat_lookup_dentry_set()
will be changed. After calling exfat_lookup_dentry_set(), if the dentry
set is not found, ->out.dev_offset will be the position of the first
empty dentry set with ->in.dentry_count empty dentries.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

lib: avoid int promotion in checksum causing signed overflow

This fixes UBSan errors during fsck like:

exfat_dir.c:522:54: runtime error: signed integer overflow: 2147483647 + 95
cannot be represented in type 'int'

Signed-off-by: Val Packett <val@packett.cool>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

mkfs: add new option -q/--quiet

This flag suppresses informative messages and prints only errors.

Signed-off-by: Pavel Reichl <preichl@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

lib: fix filename comparison

Filename comparison should include one more unicode character
if there are unused characters. Otherwise, files with the same
prefix may be found. For example, lookup a file named "19" but
returns a file named "192".

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: do not create LOST+FOUND if no orphan clusters

It is not necessary to create LOST+FOUND if no orphan clusters.
LOST+FOUND will be a zero-size directory, but the exfat in old
version of linux kernel doesn't support zero-size directory.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

Revert "tests: Add testcase for empty directory starts with zero cluster."

This reverts commit 15704469c0ee2ef1dc7a753c40db629418a40e2c.

The zero-size directory is compliant with the exFAT specification,
does not need repairing.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

Revert "fsck: Add the capability to fix zero size directory"

This reverts commit fcd68a50e104b7f3bea3d893eaa883db033e10de.

The zero-size directory is compliant with the exFAT specification,
does not need repairing.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: tests: add test for repairing duplicated filename

In tests/duplicated_name/exfat.img.tar.xz, there are 4 files
and a directory.

The files and directory:
  - file 00001: the name hash is 081e
  - file 00040: the name hash is 081e
  - file duplicated-filename-test: size is 131072 bytes
  - directory duplicated-filename-test: size is 262144 bytes
  - file duplicated-filename-test: size is 393216 bytes

We use the above files and directory to verify:
  - If the name hashes are same but the file name are not same,
    the file name will not be renamed by fsck.
  - If the file name are same, the file name will be renamed by
    fsck.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: tests: detect corruptions before repairing

If fsck can not detect that the filesystem is corrupted, the
test result still passes, which is not expected.

This commit adds detection of corruption before repairing, if
the corruption cannot be detected by fsck, the test result will
be fail.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: support fix duplicated filename in a dir

From exFAT specification, there can be no duplicate file or
directory names after up-casing within any one directory.

So this commit adds the ability to fsck to check and repair
files with the same name in a directory.

This commit check duplicate filename by comparing filename
hashes and then comparing the filenames. If there are duplicate
filename, rename to other valid names.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

lib: add exfat_lookup_file_by_utf16name()

This commit introduces a new API that looks up file by
its utf16-encoded name.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: add exfat_repair_rename_ask() to make code reusable

The renaming strategy is provided in handle_dot_dotdot_filename(),
which can be re-used in other repairs that need to be renamed.

So this commit moves the strategy into exfat_repair_rename_ask()
and rename "dot_name_num" to "invalid_name_num".

Code refinement, no functional changes.

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Wu <Andy.Wu@sony.com>
Reviewed-by: Aoyama Wataru <wataru.aoyama@sony.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: fix out-of-bounds memory access

The size of utf16_name is ENTRY_NAME_MAX, we should pass
ENTRY_NAME_MAX to exfat_utf16_len(), not ENTRY_NAME_MAX*2.

exfat_utf16_enc() returns the length of the utf16-encoded
filename, it is not needed to call exfat_utf16_len().

Signed-off-by: Yuezhang Mo <Yuezhang.Mo@sony.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

mkfs.exfat.8: document default --boundary-align & --cluster-size

mkfs.exfat.8 currently has a recommendation table from the SD association
for these two options, but does not actually describe what this program
does by default. Specifically, the default boundary alignment is fixed
at 1 MiB, and the default cluster size is set.

Signed-off-by: Mingye Wang <arthur200126@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

dump: set ui.writeable to false

Allows dump to run on read-only devices.

Signed-off-by: ianjazz246 <ianjazz246@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

commit.message:
exfatprogs: release 1.2.1 version

exfatprogs 1.2.1 - released 2023-05-17
======================================

CHANGES :
 * fsck.exfat: Repair zero size directory.
 * fsck.exfat: Four small clean-ups.

Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

fsck: fix assertion in exfat_c2o

exfat_c2o() is called with the cluster 0, and
fsck is aborted with the stack backtrace below
due to the assertion in exfat_c2o().

 exfat_c2o
 write_block
 exfat_de_iter_flush

This is caused by that write_block() could be called
for the cluster which is not read yet.

Make exfat_c2o is called only when the cluster is dirty.

Signed-off-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

lib: do not allow exfat_c2o() to return negative value

assert that clus should be >= EXFAT_FIRST_CLUSTER, instead of return
a negative value.

Acked-by: Hyunchul Lee <hyc.lee@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Erichong <erichong@qnap.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

exfat2img: fix LLVM void pointer arithmetic error

What: On LLVM and Clang with [-Werror,-Wno-pointer-arith]
void pointer arithmetic is not allowed and will cause a
compilation error.

Fix: Fix it by casting buf to (char *) before doing arithmetic.

Char * is 1 byte long, which is the same that GCC defines for void
pointer arithmetic calculations so final result is the same.

Signed-off-by: brunosampaio08 <bruno.sampaio08@unifesp.br>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>

tests: Add testcase for empty directory starts with zero cluster.

Signed-off-by: Erichong <erichong@qnap.com>
Signed-off-by: Namjae Jeon <linkinjeon@kernel.org>
